<p>was a trial one usable as a railway centre because of the shelling. Considering it got a fair shower of shells when the line was back, it is natural to suppose it would be hot now.<br/>I don't know the name of the village where we detrained, but it was between Aires &amp; Hazebrouck.  From this village we marched due south (apparently) through two other villages, to a corps reinforcement camp<br/>*The first rest camp of Australians in France on arrival from Egypt was Estrazeile. Now they are defending it.</p>
